04 January - Chicken Salad Tarts 

- 2   tablespoon water chestnuts, drained and chopped
- 1   tablespoon onion, chopped
- 6   oz white chicken
- 2   tablespoon sour cream 
- 2   tablespoon mayonnaise
- 1/4 teaspoon dill weed
- 24  slices soft white or wheat bread
- 1/4 cup butter or margarine, melted

Preheat oven to 375F. Chop water chestnuts and onion. Combine all ingredients except bread and butter in bowl. Place a small amount of this filling onto one bread slice; top with another bread slice. Brush tops with melted butter and sprinkle with dill weed. Bake 10 minutes or until golden. Serve chilled. 12 servings. 